race.description: Goulburn Soldiers Club Frank & Edna Day Mobile Pace
race.comment: DON HUGO (13) saluted two runs back then recorded an effortless win last start, scoring by 10 metres over 1609m at Menangle. May just need a bit of luck at some point from this difficult draw. Taking on a better line-up this time but he is up to the challenge. WHEREYABINBOPPIN (4) is on the radar after his last-start sixth over 1740m at Riverina Paceway two weeks ago. SWAYZEE (14) is in the mix following a respectable third at his most recent appearance over 2790m at Bathurst.
